<TITLE> Iajuddin stresses prevention against cardiac disease </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 30 (bdnews24.com)  President Iajuddin Ahmed Friday called upon cardiologists and cardiac surgeons to promote awareness and prevention of heart disease as part of the country's primary health care strategy. "I call upon you all to come forward for the benefit of the have-not section of society," he said. Speaking at an international conference on "Updates on Management in Cardiology and Cardiac Surgery", organised by Labaid Cardiac Hospital, Iajuddin said the high costs of treatment underscored the importance of prevention especially for the poor. The president said advances in cardiac therapy should be bolstered by added research in the causes and prevention of cardiac disease. Health adviser ASM Matiur Rahman and Labaid Cardiac Hospital managing director MA Shamim were present at the opening ceremony of the conference at Sheraton Hotel that brings together cardiologists and cardiac surgeons from home 
